# Tools – AI Dev Suite, RAG

## Not deployed to Netlify

This repo (zerwiz/setup) is never pushed to Netlify. Tools are delivered via curl from zerwiz/setup.

## Documentation

- All tool docs live in **`doc/`**.
- Each tool dir keeps a brief README pointing to `doc/<name>/`.
- Structure: `doc/ai-dev-suite/` (incl. `rag/`).
- **When changing a tool:** Update the relevant doc. Add new docs when adding features (e.g. STORAGE.md, FUNCTIONS.md).

## Extra programs (AI Dev Suite, Workshop Setup)

- **Location:** This repo (zerwiz/setup) at root: ai-dev-suite/ (incl. rag/), debugger/, setup.sh, run-tui.sh, start-*.sh.
- **Deployed from:** zerwiz/setup. Push directly here.
- **Curl commands** must point to zerwiz/setup only.

## AI Dev Suite – system portability

The install must work on any user machine:

- **Install script:** Support `AI_DEV_SUITE_DIR`, `XDG_DATA_HOME`, `AI_DEV_SUITE_BIN_DIR`. Use `$HOME` or `$USERPROFILE` (Windows).
- **Elixir config:** Use `HOME` or `USERPROFILE` for memory/drive.
- **Paths:** Install dir (code) ≠ config dir (user data). Config: `~/.config/ai-dev-suite`. Never hardcode paths.

## Adding a new tool

1. Create `<name>/` with `install.sh` and README (at repo root)
2. Add doc in `doc/<name>/`
3. Add terminal block or link if curl-able
